1. Ona *kontroliše* sve račune u firmi. (She controls all the accounts in the company.)
2. *Kontrolišem* svoje misli da bih se fokusirao na ono što je važno. (I control my thoughts in order to focus on what's important.)
3. Kada policija dođe, oni će *kontrolisati* svakoga u sobi. (When the police arrive, they will check everyone in the room.)
4. Da bi se sprečila šteta, treba *kontrolisati* ulaz i izlaz iz zgrade. (To prevent damage, we need to monitor the entrance and exit of the building.)
5. Da li si siguran da ćeš moći *kontrolisati* situaciju ako dođe do problema? (Are you sure you'll be able to handle the situation if there's a problem?)
6. Naša kompanija *kontroliše* kvalitet svakog proizvoda pre nego što ga pustimo na tržište. (Our company checks the quality of every product before we release it to the market.)
7. Učitelj *kontroliše* znanje učenika na kraju svakog poglavlja. (The teacher assesses the students' knowledge at the end of each chapter.)
8. Kada vozite, uvek treba da *kontrolišete* brzinu i pazite na druge vozače. (When you're driving, you should always monitor your speed and watch out for other drivers.)
9. Država ima pravo da *kontroliše* medije u cilju očuvanja javnog interesa. (The government has the right to regulate the media in order to protect the public interest.)
10. Radnici će biti *kontrolisani* tokom cele smene kako bi se osigurala produktivnost. (Workers will be supervised throughout the shift to ensure productivity.)